Feisty, huh?

281
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,440
It's all your fault!

282
00:25:04,480 --> 00:25:05,960
It's all because of you!

283
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:32,540
[I left to buy some coffee]

284
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:35,860
[You don't need to wake up early. Rest up]

285
00:25:35,880 --> 00:25:39,180
[You don't have to come to the farm today]

286
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:45,800
[Mok]

287
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:19,160
Saitharn.

288
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:21,560
How are you?

289
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:22,800
Hey...

290
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,200
where's Saeng and Pawn?

291
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,600
- Hey!
- Calm down, take it easy.

292
00:26:29,660 --> 00:26:31,120
Pawn is safe.

293
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:37,400
Wait, what about Saeng then?

294
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,380
Saeng... is he okay?

295
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:41,460
Answer me.

296
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,360
- Is he alright?
- Saitharn.

297
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:49,880
Saeng went into
the operating room yesterday.

298
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:54,160
The doctor said the bullet struck
his left shoulder, hitting a major artery.

299
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:57,080
That made the operation quite complicated.

300
00:26:58,120 --> 00:27:00,200
He just came out of
the operating room this morning.

301
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:04,080
But...

302
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,480
But what?

303
00:27:09,340 --> 00:27:10,440
What happened to Saeng?

304
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:15,520
He is still unconscious.

305
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,680
He hasn't woken up.

306
00:27:19,740 --> 00:27:21,620
- The doctor said...
- It's my fault.

307
00:27:28,180 --> 00:27:30,640
I always make everything worse.

308
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:37,560
Why did I come here?

309
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,920
It's always like this wherever I go.

310
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:44,480
I loved Phayu so much,

311
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,600
but I still couldn't save him.

312
00:27:49,840 --> 00:27:50,800
There's Pawn.

313
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:53,440
And then Saeng...

314
00:27:55,960 --> 00:27:58,600
The people I love got hurt
because of me again.

315
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:03,120
I'm the problem here.

316
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,300
Mom was right.

317
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,640
- Hey.
- You...

318
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:10,960
I know

319
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,160
you think I'm not to blame...

320
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:17,040
that it's not my fault.

321
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:20,400
But it's the truth.

322
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,840
- Don't cry.
- It's my fault.

323
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:26,480
It's my fault.

324
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:33,240
It's my fault...

325
00:28:34,900 --> 00:28:36,360
It's my fault...

326
00:28:58,640 --> 00:28:59,600
Oh, Gale.

327
00:28:59,900 --> 00:29:01,140
You haven't gone to see Phae yet?

328
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:02,560
I'm about to go now.

329
00:29:03,140 --> 00:29:05,360
There's so much stuff to take with me here.

330
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:10,120
Oh, Saitharn,

331
00:29:10,500 --> 00:29:11,560
you're awake?

332
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,480
Yes, hello.

333
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:18,920
I'm glad you're okay.

334
00:29:19,140 --> 00:29:20,700
I heard about what happened last night.

335
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:21,960
It really shook me.

336
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,360
You're not hurt anywhere, right?

337
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:28,920
Yes.

338
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:31,860
Oh, Saitharn.

339
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,880
This is Gale, she's my cousin.

340
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:36,400
She'll be around to work on
her fashion show project.

341
00:29:39,420 --> 00:29:40,840
I have never seen you

342
00:29:41,100 --> 00:29:44,400
take care of someone like this before, Sila.

343
00:29:47,580 --> 00:29:49,560
Right, are you guys about to leave?

344
00:29:50,140 --> 00:29:51,760
Can I ask you to buy some fruit for me?

345
00:29:51,860 --> 00:29:53,960
I don't think Saeng-La
can eat anything just yet.

346
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:55,300
He hasn't recovered yet.

347
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:57,140
Who said it's for him?

348
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,480
I wanted to give it to Mok.

349
00:29:58,660 --> 00:30:00,660
He hasn't eaten since yesterday, I think.

350
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:03,800
Oh, it'd be great
if you bought some vitamins for Mok too.

351
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:07,080
He doesn't look so well.

352
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:08,960
Okay.

353
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:11,640
I'll go there after I finish my work.

354
00:30:11,700 --> 00:30:12,520
Take care.

355
00:30:19,140 --> 00:30:19,920
Let's go.

356
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:40,600
Saeng...

357
00:30:42,360 --> 00:30:43,280
You know,

358
00:30:44,340 --> 00:30:45,680
I'm too scared to sleep.

359
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:50,680
I'm so afraid my nightmare will come true.

360
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:57,480
That I'll lose you.

361
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:05,200
I thought you could handle anything...

362
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:09,320
Just wake up already.

363
00:31:11,360 --> 00:31:12,860
A jerk like you

364
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,360
being this quiet

365
00:31:16,020 --> 00:31:17,440
just isn't like you at all.

366
00:31:21,360 --> 00:31:23,040
So wake up and talk to me already.

367
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:30,220
Who are you calling a jerk?

368
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,800
Hey, Saeng.

369
00:31:32,460 --> 00:31:33,520
You're awake.

370
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:34,800
Water...

371
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:36,640
- Give me water.
- Water!

372
00:31:37,110 --> 00:31:38,080
Water...

373
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:39,880
Water.

374
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:51,800
Sit up first.

375
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:09,840
What? Why are you staring at me so much?

376
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,440
I'm so glad

377
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:13,800
you woke up.

378
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:19,600
Seriously.

379
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:25,560
I thought I was going to lose you for good.

380
00:32:29,060 --> 00:32:30,640
I can't even imagine

381
00:32:31,320 --> 00:32:32,520
if I don't have you...

382
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:39,800
What are you even on about?

383
00:32:40,580 --> 00:32:42,720
Is this what I get after I just woke up?

384
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:44,680
Ugh...

385
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:47,040
I'd rather go back to sleep.

386
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:49,040
Ow, ow, ow!

387
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:49,880
I'm sorry.

388
00:32:50,120 --> 00:32:51,840
- I just had surgery.
- My bad.

389
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:54,440
Should I call the nurse for you?

390
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:57,920
You dummy.

391
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:01,040
I'm also glad I'm still alive.

392
00:33:03,900 --> 00:33:05,200
And I'm glad

393
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:07,640
you're the first person I woke up to talk to.

394
00:33:23,740 --> 00:33:24,680
Boss.

395
00:33:26,740 --> 00:33:27,920
Saitharn.

396
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:35,280
Is there anything you brought over for me?

397
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:38,680
Saeng...

398
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:42,880
Are you still hurting anywhere? I...

399
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:45,480
I'm sorry.

400
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:49,400
Saitharn, listen to me.

401
00:33:50,040 --> 00:33:51,520
I'm okay now.

402
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:53,360
You don't have to worry.

403
00:33:54,580 --> 00:33:57,240
I feel like I just had a really good sleep.

404
00:33:57,520 --> 00:34:00,960
I've never slept this much before, you know?

405
00:34:04,340 --> 00:34:07,100
He's glad he doesn't have to
work at the farm.

406
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,159
It works out for him.

407
00:34:09,199 --> 00:34:10,679
But I...

408
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:12,800
I'm so sorry, Saeng.

409
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:16,199
I didn't want this to happen.

410
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:20,780
I think they wanted to hurt us all.

411
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:21,840
Saitharn,

412
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:24,120
listen to me.

413
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:26,280
What happened last night

414
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,560
shouldn't have happened to anyone,

415
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:30,080
whether it was me,

416
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,560
the others on the farm,

417
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:33,080
or you.

418
00:34:36,300 --> 00:34:39,040
But I know if it were you,

419
00:34:40,679 --> 00:34:42,480
you would have done the same thing, right?

420
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:51,120
Come.

421
00:34:56,639 --> 00:34:58,040
I'm sorry.

422
00:34:58,260 --> 00:34:59,960
It's okay.

423
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,240
Boss.

424
00:35:04,020 --> 00:35:05,080
About...

425
00:35:05,540 --> 00:35:10,480
the intruders who broke in and attacked us,

426
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,200
have they been caught?

427
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,240
Don't worry,

428
00:35:15,700 --> 00:35:17,360
they won't be able to hurt anybody again.

429
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:21,640
And I will not let the one behind this
get away with it.

430
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:27,920
Can I have the food you brought now?

431
00:35:28,060 --> 00:35:29,640
Did the doctor say you could eat yet?

432
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:32,040
Yeah, the doctor gave me the okay.

433
00:35:41,140 --> 00:35:42,260
The older you get,

434
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:45,560
the less I expect from you.

435
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:47,520
So,

436
00:35:48,160 --> 00:35:50,800
how will you help me take over
Phusangdao Farm?

437
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:57,080
You sent your men

438
00:35:57,180 --> 00:35:59,400
to kidnap Sila's newcomer.

439
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,920
It was such a simple plan,

440
00:36:04,060 --> 00:36:05,600
yet you still failed.

441
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:08,320
Disappointing.

442
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:11,600
It...

443
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:13,440
It...

444
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,960
won't happen again, father.

445
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:17,600
I promise.

446
00:36:17,620 --> 00:36:18,960
Enough with the empty promises, Manmuang.

447
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:22,680
Show me what you can do already.

448
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:26,920
Perhaps in this life,

449
00:36:26,950 --> 00:36:28,240
I don't think

450
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:32,120
I'll live to see
my son defeat Sila even once.

451
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:40,760
As for closing the deal,

452
00:36:41,260 --> 00:36:42,360
you can forget it.

453
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:44,840
I'll let my men take care of it.

454
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:50,640
Does this mean...?

455
00:36:51,400 --> 00:36:52,800
Just do as I say.

456
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,520
And stop asking things.

457
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:00,480
Yes.

458
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:03,120
Get out.

459
00:38:12,380 --> 00:38:13,280
Hey, Muang!

460
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:15,680
Let's take pictures.

461
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:23,440
Here,

462
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:25,800
a graduation gift from me.

463
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:28,160
No need.

464
00:38:29,620 --> 00:38:32,040
I just wanted to
congratulate us on graduating.

465
00:38:33,380 --> 00:38:34,920
And that I'm proud of you.

466
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:40,880
Proud?

467
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:45,240
Even my father

468
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:47,680
isn't proud of me.

469
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,240
Who the hell do you think you are?

470
00:38:52,340 --> 00:38:53,760
I know how you feel,

471
00:38:55,340 --> 00:38:57,840
but deep down,
Uncle is definitely proud of you.

472
00:38:58,040 --> 00:38:58,860
You did your best.

473
00:38:58,880 --> 00:39:00,920
Don't act like you know my father.

474
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:05,120
You're talented,

475
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:07,320
and people love you.

476
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:09,760
Muang,

477
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:12,200
I'm your friend, alright?

478
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:14,800
Friend?

479
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:18,760
Every time I hear your name,

480
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:22,500
I keep hearing my father’s voice
saying it in my head,

481
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:23,900
and it's driving me f*cking nuts!

482
00:39:25,080 --> 00:39:27,240
Do you know what
it feels like to be your friend?

483
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:31,320
It feels like I'm just a shadow.

484
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:34,900
And I'm f*cking sick of
being in your shadow.

485
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:35,840
Muang!

486
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:39,040
You know I never wanted
to compete with you.

487
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:40,600
Then how should I feel, huh?

488
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:42,720
Every time people praised you,

489
00:39:43,680 --> 00:39:45,520
my father would look at me

490
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:48,280
and say, "Look at your friend."

491
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:50,480
You already have everything.

492
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:53,280
I don't want to live in a world
where I'm always in your shadow anymore.

493
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:54,360
Listen to me.

494
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:56,920
- I never think of you like that.
- From now on,

495
00:39:57,680 --> 00:40:00,320
I'll spend the rest of
my life to bring you down, Sila.

496
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:05,440
Muang.

497
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:08,040
Muang!

498
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:34,080
Muang,

499
00:40:34,240 --> 00:40:35,880
I'm about to go meet up with Gale.

500
00:40:35,980 --> 00:40:37,620
Do you want to go together?

501
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:39,800
I heard from Dad that
you're going to the city.

502
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:41,760
Phae,

503
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:46,480
are you still working on
that stupid project with that farm?

504
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:49,020
Have you ever listened to what I've said?

505
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:50,280
Don't say that, Muang.

506
00:40:50,540 --> 00:40:52,800
I already told you I don't want to
have any problem with Sila.

507
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:55,720
- I just want to...
- Sila, Sila, Sila.

508
00:40:55,860 --> 00:40:57,240
What the f*ck is it with this name?

509
00:40:57,720 --> 00:40:59,640
I'm f*cking tired of hearing it.

510
00:41:01,100 --> 00:41:02,300
This is exactly why.

511
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:03,920
It's because you're like this, Phae,

512
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:07,520
self-centered, selfish,
and only caring about your own happiness.

513
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,120
Do you have any idea
what our family had to sacrifice?!

514
00:41:11,140 --> 00:41:14,680
No wonder Dad never
expects anything from you.

515
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:17,400
All you do is waste your time
on meaningless things.

516
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:23,660
What?

517
00:41:23,680 --> 00:41:24,600
Muang...

518
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:25,520
What?!

519
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:29,000
Go on, tell me I'm wrong!

520
00:41:30,340 --> 00:41:32,180
If you'd married Sila,

521
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:34,000
if you'd done what Dad told you to,

522
00:41:34,020 --> 00:41:36,280
our family wouldn't
be struggling like this.

523
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:38,080
Damn useless!

524
00:41:38,180 --> 00:41:41,520
Do you know who's been taking responsibility
for everything you’ve never made use of?

525
00:41:41,940 --> 00:41:43,180
Me!

526
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:45,440
I'm the one cleaning up
your f*cking mess all the time!

527
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:49,760
I'm the one always blamed for your failure!

528
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:54,320
And yet you're
the only one living your happy life!

529
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:55,760
Damn it all!

530
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:23,120
[Phusangdao Group]

531
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:30,840
Mueanphae,

532
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:32,920
can I see the latest draft?

533
00:42:46,180 --> 00:42:47,000
Phae.

534
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:51,940
Phae.

535
00:42:54,300 --> 00:42:55,400
Yes, Gale?

536
00:42:57,120 --> 00:42:58,320
Are you okay?

537
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:02,720
Did you get any sleep last night?

538
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:06,280
Or did I give you too much work to handle?

539
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:10,280
It's not that, Gale.

540
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:15,640
I'm just thinking about something.

541
00:43:22,760 --> 00:43:23,920
You're lying.

542
00:43:25,880 --> 00:43:27,560
Why do you think I won't notice?

543
00:43:29,280 --> 00:43:31,400
This is the first time
I see you spacing out.

544
00:43:32,060 --> 00:43:33,960
You're normally so focused on your work.

545
00:43:40,240 --> 00:43:42,360
You can tell me anything.

546
00:43:43,860 --> 00:43:45,080
I'm here to listen.

547
00:43:56,500 --> 00:43:57,440
Well...

548
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:04,120
I got into an argument with my family.

549
00:44:13,380 --> 00:44:14,760
I don't know

550
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:16,720
that...

551
00:44:17,240 --> 00:44:18,420
since

552
00:44:19,420 --> 00:44:20,860
when did my family

553
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:24,000
and Sila's farm

554
00:44:24,540 --> 00:44:25,910
turn into this?

555
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,640
When I was younger,

556
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:32,720
I remember

557
00:44:32,740 --> 00:44:35,600
Sila being like an older brother to me.

558
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:41,200
Manmuang, Mueanphae, Sila.

559
00:44:41,220 --> 00:44:42,720
Come have some fruit.

560
00:44:43,880 --> 00:44:46,760
My parents, uncle, and aunt

561
00:44:47,140 --> 00:44:49,720
would take turns
taking us out to different places,

562
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:51,280
sometimes for meals.

563
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:54,520
Some months, we'd all go together.

564
00:44:55,780 --> 00:44:57,440
It was really nice back then

565
00:44:58,440 --> 00:45:00,440
since we always stayed together.

566
00:45:00,840 --> 00:45:04,400
Maybe it's because
our fathers both own a farm,

567
00:45:04,840 --> 00:45:06,600
so they have a lot to talk about.

568
00:45:07,560 --> 00:45:08,800
I remember

569
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:11,320
Dad and Uncle often talking about

570
00:45:11,620 --> 00:45:15,080
merging both our farms into one.

571
00:45:15,620 --> 00:45:17,440
We were very happy back then

572
00:45:18,020 --> 00:45:20,120
because we felt like real siblings.

573
00:45:20,940 --> 00:45:24,120
We thought it would be nice
to live in the same house,

574
00:45:24,260 --> 00:45:25,800
playing together every day,

575
00:45:25,940 --> 00:45:27,440
without having to wait
for Dad to take me there.

576
00:45:29,880 --> 00:45:31,120
Dad said,

577
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:33,000
in the future,

578
00:45:33,480 --> 00:45:35,480
these two rings would be ours.

579
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:38,840
I was very confused then.

580
00:45:40,880 --> 00:45:42,640
There were three of us,

581
00:45:42,780 --> 00:45:44,320
so how could two rings

582
00:45:44,560 --> 00:45:45,800
be enough?

583
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:47,400
Dad.

584
00:45:48,280 --> 00:45:49,080
Dad!

585
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:52,040
I don't have those feelings for Sila.

586
00:45:52,560 --> 00:45:55,760
When will you stop asking me
to go have dinner with him?

587
00:45:56,120 --> 00:45:56,920
Huh?

588
00:45:57,260 --> 00:45:59,380
Did you know how uncomfortable it was?

589
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:01,280
It's just a meal!

590
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:05,000
How many times has it been already, Dad?

591
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:07,280
The truth is,

592
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:09,880
Dad had planned this all along.

593
00:46:10,320 --> 00:46:12,480
He wanted me and Sila to marry

594
00:46:13,260 --> 00:46:15,600
in order to merge the two families.

595
00:46:16,320 --> 00:46:17,720
But you understand, right?

596
00:46:18,140 --> 00:46:19,480
For me,

597
00:46:20,400 --> 00:46:22,880
Sila is like my brother.

598
00:46:27,140 --> 00:46:29,040
After Uncle passed away,

599
00:46:31,160 --> 00:46:33,160
my father became even more pushy.

600
00:46:38,760 --> 00:46:40,600
And the strange thing is,

601
00:46:42,040 --> 00:46:43,640
I don't know

602
00:46:44,960 --> 00:46:46,240
since when

603
00:46:47,540 --> 00:46:48,760
Manmuang

604
00:46:50,680 --> 00:46:52,280
and Sila stopped talking to each other.

605
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:55,680
And now...

606
00:46:56,680 --> 00:46:58,240
they don't really see eye to eye anymore.

607
00:47:03,340 --> 00:47:04,120
But...

608
00:47:07,240 --> 00:47:09,640
I think it was when
I was studying in France.

609
00:47:18,860 --> 00:47:20,360
Muang wasn't the only one

610
00:47:20,720 --> 00:47:22,280
who stopped talking to Sila.

611
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:29,960
When it was all over,

612
00:47:33,280 --> 00:47:35,000
I was so relieved.

613
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:40,120
About how I don't have to see Dad,

614
00:47:40,940 --> 00:47:42,000
Mom,

615
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:43,940
Muang,

616
00:47:46,900 --> 00:47:48,440
and even Sila.

617
00:47:52,460 --> 00:47:54,900
It was great.

618
00:47:57,940 --> 00:47:59,300
I felt amazing,

619
00:48:01,440 --> 00:48:04,080
not having to be in
an uncomfortable situation like that.

620
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:21,160
Especially when I was with Sila,

621
00:48:27,060 --> 00:48:30,200
I didn't have to act

622
00:48:30,480 --> 00:48:32,480
the way my parents expected me to.

623
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:37,380
When I first arrived in Thailand,

624
00:48:37,400 --> 00:48:39,400
the only person
who came to pick me up was Sila,

625
00:48:40,360 --> 00:48:42,720
while my family had forgotten
about my arrival that day.

626
00:48:43,920 --> 00:48:45,760
It made me realize

627
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:47,480
that, all this time,

628
00:48:47,780 --> 00:48:50,800
why had I been trying so hard
to meet my parents' expectations

629
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:54,600
when someone I deeply
cared about, like Sila,

630
00:48:55,280 --> 00:48:56,840
was the one who cared about me the most?

631
00:48:57,080 --> 00:48:57,920
Yes, Mom?

632
00:48:58,320 --> 00:48:59,760
How are you doing?

633
00:48:59,960 --> 00:49:02,280
Have you arrived at Phusangdao Farm?

634
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:04,280
I think I'll get there very soon.

635
00:49:04,480 --> 00:49:06,840
If you're bringing stuff to Sila's mom,

636
00:49:06,900 --> 00:49:08,980
don't forget to go into his farm as well.

637
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:12,120
Give him the fruit and necktie
I prepared for you.

638
00:49:13,780 --> 00:49:15,800
Dad! Stop it.

639
00:49:15,940 --> 00:49:17,160
Stop doing this, please.

640
00:49:24,160 --> 00:49:24,840
Ugh.

641
00:49:25,180 --> 00:49:26,120
Ah!

642
00:49:33,140 --> 00:49:36,240
I never feel like I belong here, Gale.

643
00:49:43,620 --> 00:49:44,920
The older I get,

644
00:49:46,680 --> 00:49:47,800
the more I feel like

645
00:49:49,080 --> 00:49:50,280
I'm just

646
00:49:51,020 --> 00:49:53,160
a pawn or something

647
00:49:53,880 --> 00:49:54,560
that...

648
00:49:55,160 --> 00:49:57,320
has to follow their parents' order.

649
00:50:02,520 --> 00:50:03,280
As if...

650
00:50:03,880 --> 00:50:05,440
everything I've done

651
00:50:10,460 --> 00:50:12,780
has never made them proud.

652
00:50:15,780 --> 00:50:16,800
Never.

653
00:50:26,540 --> 00:50:28,920
The only way I can make them proud

654
00:50:35,260 --> 00:50:37,900
is to marry Sila, right?

655
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:57,480
But I'm proud of you.

656
00:51:05,520 --> 00:51:07,320
If I had a daughter like you,

657
00:51:08,120 --> 00:51:09,740
who is kind,

658
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:12,360
dedicated,

659
00:51:14,020 --> 00:51:16,200
and loves her family this much,

660
00:51:18,220 --> 00:51:20,120
how could I not be proud of you?

661
00:51:25,960 --> 00:51:27,280
I don't know

662
00:51:28,280 --> 00:51:31,000
what happened here in the past

663
00:51:31,340 --> 00:51:32,720
and what it's all about.

664
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:37,560
But from what
I've heard from Sila about you,

665
00:51:39,020 --> 00:51:40,720
rest assured,

666
00:51:41,180 --> 00:51:43,720
that even if there's no one
who's proud of you,

667
00:51:45,080 --> 00:51:46,720
you still have Sila

668
00:51:48,080 --> 00:51:49,120
and me

669
00:51:52,220 --> 00:51:54,480
who will acknowledge all your efforts,

670
00:51:57,160 --> 00:51:59,000
recognize your potential,

671
00:52:04,040 --> 00:52:05,600
and see that you

672
00:52:07,920 --> 00:52:10,360
deserve to be appreciated the most.

673
00:52:53,040 --> 00:52:55,200
Where should I put the cloth, Ms. Gale?

674
00:52:56,440 --> 00:52:57,720
You can put it on the table.

675
00:52:57,960 --> 00:52:58,880
I'll go grab it later.

676
00:53:22,080 --> 00:53:23,000
Okay,

677
00:53:25,340 --> 00:53:27,480
I'll help you with this.

678
00:53:37,380 --> 00:53:39,380
Thank you so much, Gale.

679
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:44,640
Sometimes...

680
00:53:47,940 --> 00:53:50,160
I forget

681
00:53:51,560 --> 00:53:53,320
that I have you by my side.

682
00:54:00,380 --> 00:54:02,160
No matter what,

683
00:54:06,640 --> 00:54:08,160
you're not alone, okay?

684
00:54:38,460 --> 00:54:39,080
Saeng.

685
00:54:39,980 --> 00:54:41,220
Did you forget anything?

686
00:54:41,380 --> 00:54:42,960
I told you not to carry anything.

687
00:54:43,100 --> 00:54:44,680
- Fine.
- Let me carry it!

688
00:54:45,380 --> 00:54:46,300
Why are you so stubborn?!

689
00:54:48,460 --> 00:54:49,800
- I'll carry it.
- Thanks, doggo.

690
00:54:50,620 --> 00:54:52,440
How many times do
I have to say this?

691
00:54:52,620 --> 00:54:53,800
Ugh!

692
00:54:55,260 --> 00:54:56,440
You two.

693
00:54:56,580 --> 00:54:58,040
My head still hurts.

694
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:01,960
Come help me, too.
These aren't even my things.

695
00:55:03,460 --> 00:55:04,160
Hmph.

696
00:55:05,180 --> 00:55:06,380
Let's go.

697
00:55:06,400 --> 00:55:08,640
Oh, these kids.

698
00:55:13,260 --> 00:55:14,440
- It's okay.
- Ugh!

699
00:55:15,020 --> 00:55:16,440
Hurry up and get over here.

700
00:55:17,060 --> 00:55:19,360
And stop making a sad cat face like that.

701
00:55:21,820 --> 00:55:24,980
- But everyone got hurt because of me.
- Oh, stop it.

702
00:55:25,520 --> 00:55:27,640
You don't have to feel bad for everything.

703
00:55:27,860 --> 00:55:29,760
Just let go of the bad things,

704
00:55:30,100 --> 00:55:31,680
and hold on to the good things.

705
00:55:31,700 --> 00:55:35,080
Like how beautiful Paula is.

706
00:55:36,740 --> 00:55:39,560
Oh, and there's also Boss's beautiful farm.

707
00:55:42,260 --> 00:55:43,320
Because this place

708
00:55:44,460 --> 00:55:46,000
is like your home now.

709
00:55:53,780 --> 00:55:56,480
Hey, I'm getting goosebumps!

710
00:55:56,740 --> 00:55:58,440
It's so unlike you.

711
00:56:00,780 --> 00:56:02,440
Oh, Boss,

712
00:56:02,760 --> 00:56:05,740
the workers want to hold
a blessing ceremony.

713
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:06,920
What do you think?

714
00:56:08,560 --> 00:56:09,240
Alright,

715
00:56:09,640 --> 00:56:11,440
I'll tell Chakkrit to
pick an auspicious date.

716
00:56:14,640 --> 00:56:15,280
Let's go.

717
00:56:21,560 --> 00:56:22,840
Yes, Ms. Wipa?

718
00:56:23,120 --> 00:56:24,200
Mr. Sila,

719
00:56:24,260 --> 00:56:26,400
can you come to
the meeting room right away?

720
00:56:26,540 --> 00:56:28,840
There's an important guest
who wants to meet you.

721
00:56:46,780 --> 00:56:47,680
Hello.

722
00:56:49,240 --> 00:56:50,440
Hello.

723
00:56:51,600 --> 00:56:53,200
Is there something important

724
00:56:55,380 --> 00:56:59,080
that requires the head of Khum Rimpha
to come all the way here?

725
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:34,600
I feel better.

726
00:57:34,780 --> 00:57:37,320
But that doesn't mean

727
00:57:37,680 --> 00:57:38,760
I'm "okay".

728
00:57:40,200 --> 00:57:42,640
You can blame yourself
as much as you want.

729
00:57:43,040 --> 00:57:46,460
But I want you to know
I would never judge you by your past

730
00:57:46,480 --> 00:57:48,080
or what you've been through.

731
00:57:49,280 --> 00:57:52,260
Have you ever thought about how
Sila and I gave you the chance to work here again?

732
00:57:52,280 --> 00:57:54,620
But we've been overworked for
the entire month now, Ms. Wipa.

733
00:57:54,640 --> 00:57:56,440
It was just a small mistake.

734
00:57:56,460 --> 00:57:58,360
Why are you blaming us for everything?

735
00:57:58,380 --> 00:57:59,200
Silence!

736
00:58:15,520 --> 00:58:21,340
♫I wanna thank you for making me feel♫

737
00:58:21,380 --> 00:58:24,960
♫Just how beautiful love can be♫

738
00:58:24,980 --> 00:58:27,200
♫Every chamber of my heart♫

739
00:58:27,220 --> 00:58:29,840
♫Will be yours from now on♫

740
00:58:29,860 --> 00:58:35,500
♫You're a godsent present from above♫

741
00:58:35,700 --> 00:58:41,520
♫I'll always belong to you evermore♫

742
00:58:41,540 --> 00:58:47,740
♫My heart will always be yours forever♫

